Remarks. This species is similar to
Phyllocoptruta oleivora ( Ashmead)
, 1879 , but can be differentiated by coxal area I with granules (coxal area smooth in
P . oleivora
), prodorsal shield without granules laterally and the dorsal design didn’t forming the net (prodorsal shield with granules laterally and dorsal design forming the net pattern in
P . oleivora
), accessory setae 4 (accessory setae very short in
P . oleivora
), empodium 4 - rayed (empodium 5 -rayed in
P . oleivora
).
